1
00:00:30,720 --> 00:00:32,960
Li

2
00:00:32,960 --> 00:00:33,720
Li Yang.

3
00:01:04,360 --> 00:01:05,040
Liu.

4
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:37,920
What the hell?

5
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:38,759
Brother, what are you doing here?

6
00:01:38,759 --> 00:01:40,020
Do you know how to play?

7
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:45,080
Yes, that's fine.

8
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:03,250
Let's go.

9
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:09,120
I understand.

10
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,860
You're here to avenge him?

11
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:13,640
He's such an honest person.

12
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:15,040
Why did you mess with him?

13
00:02:24,079 --> 00:02:26,200
Look at how you people are dressed.

14
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:29,280
You must be wanderers too, right?

15
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:31,760
Since we're all wanderers...

16
00:02:31,760 --> 00:02:33,760
You should know the rules of the game.

17
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:34,840
Always leave someone a way out.

18
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:36,840
So you can face each other in the future.

19
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:38,079
But this guy...

20
00:02:38,079 --> 00:02:39,880
He had to take everything from me.

21
00:02:39,880 --> 00:02:41,200
Left me with just a lone king and still beat me.

22
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,840
Isn't he just picking a fight?

23
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:43,960
Right? Was it you?

24
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:47,570
Was it you or not?

25
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:54,060
Come, sit down.

26
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:00,800
Your chess skills are terrible.

27
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:02,260
Who can you blame for that?

28
00:03:03,160 --> 00:03:04,360
Did you hit him?

29
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:05,960
Yeah, so what?

30
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:08,000
Apologize to him.

31
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:11,160
Pay for his medical expenses and it's over.

32
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:28,200
I haven't laid a hand on you yet.

33
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:31,760
Don't you understand what's going on?

34
00:03:31,760 --> 00:03:34,000
Look at these guys standing behind you.

35
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:35,600
What a mess they are.

36
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:36,930
What a state they're in.

37
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,079
I just heard all that crashing noise.

38
00:03:38,079 --> 00:03:39,740
Did you come bouncing in here?

39
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:41,079
What if I actually

40
00:03:41,079 --> 00:03:43,000
beat you guys up for real?

41
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:44,520
If you go to the police

42
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:47,050
and get that so-called forensic assessment,

43
00:03:47,079 --> 00:03:48,200
I couldn't explain

44
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:50,160
which of your injuries I caused.

45
00:03:53,079 --> 00:03:53,840
I've taken photos

46
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:54,880
of his injuries.

47
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:55,840
If he gets any more injuries,

48
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,280
then you're the one who did it.

49
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:58,880
You're asking for it, buddy.

50
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:01,080
My new camera is coming in handy.

51
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:02,720
Let me take another shot.

52
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:03,650
I need evidence.

53
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:06,280
I'll deal with you later.

54
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:08,840
Look at you two, one with a cracked head.

55
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:09,960
One with a limp.

56
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:11,760
So this is the

57
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:13,760
crippled one, right?

58
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:15,530
My name is Huo Dongfeng.

59
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:18,440
What did he say?

60
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:20,240
He said his name is Huo Dongfeng.

61
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:27,040
The leader of the Three Heroes of Dalin,

62
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:28,160
Huo Dongfeng.

63
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:31,400
Didn't you just get out?

64
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:32,600
A little over a month.

65
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:35,080
Then you're really something.

66
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:36,840
Really. But now that we've met,

67
00:04:37,159 --> 00:04:38,720
you haven't been out long either.

68
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:39,320
To be honest,

69
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:41,250
I don't have many days left myself.

70
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:45,600
See this?

71
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:48,200
My intestines

72
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:50,280
got badly damaged in a fight.

73
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:52,560
Western doctors said I wouldn't survive.

74
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,440
My family

75
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:54,760
found a quack doctor

76
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:56,360
who replaced them with dog intestines.

77
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:58,490
Since I don't have long to live anyway,

78
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:00,600
why should I care who you are?

79
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:03,840
Try that again.

80
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:05,080
The way you talk

81
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:06,210
is really annoying.

82
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:07,920
You look like a howling dog

83
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:09,650
and your yapping hurts my ears.

84
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:12,760
Let's not waste time

85
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:13,960
with this nonsense.

86
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:15,320
Just tell me the truth,

87
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:16,920
why did you come looking for me today?

88
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:18,080
For a fight, right?

89
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:18,920
So what now?

90
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:19,840
Just these few people?

91
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:22,370
Should I wait for you to call reinforcements?

92
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:25,400
Let me say something.

93
00:05:31,440 --> 00:05:32,360
Um...

94
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:34,960
Are you going to film him?

95
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:38,040
Could you do that again first?

96
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:42,960
Better to have evidence.

97
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:43,360
Keep some proof.

98
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,620
You're worse than him.

99
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:47,200
No, I think we can all reach an agreement, right?

100
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:48,600
You set up this chess game

101
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,480
to resolve this peacefully.

102
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:51,920
There's no need to get physical.

103
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:52,980
It's unnecessary.

104
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:54,360
Let's

105
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:55,320
play a round,

106
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:56,159
shall we?

107
00:05:56,159 --> 00:05:57,560
Are you blind?

108
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:58,680
Can't you see what's going on?

109
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:00,080
This has nothing to do with chess now.

110
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:01,200
Besides, when two cats are fighting,

111
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:02,720
what business does a rat like you have trying to mediate?

112
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:03,560
Get lost.

113
00:06:26,280 --> 00:06:27,760
Let me summarize briefly.

114
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,840
Today we fought

115
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:31,840
a perfect, beautiful victory.

116
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:33,040
Right. First, in terms of teamwork,

117
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:34,240
with my brother and me leading,

118
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:34,720
That's right.

119
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:35,360
My brother kicked him,

120
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:36,280
and I immediately followed with my fist.

121
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:38,000
That Gouchang was completely defenseless.

122
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:38,880
Two quick hits.

123
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:39,840
He couldn't even touch us.

124
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:40,520
Right.

125
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:42,120
This Gouchang,

126
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:44,240
looks like a barking hound.

127
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,840
I didn't even want to bother with him.

128
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:47,040
If it wasn't for you,

129
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,240
I would have walked away.

130
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:50,570
My brother didn't even want to beat him up.

131
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:52,560
Weren't you doing it for Erpang?

132
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:53,280
I...

133
00:06:55,159 --> 00:06:56,840
For Erpang,

134
00:06:56,840 --> 00:06:57,240
right?

135
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:58,240
Erpang.

136
00:06:59,240 --> 00:06:59,640
Let me tell you,

137
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:01,000
Erpang himself

138
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,240
could have solved this problem on his own.

139
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:03,240
You're bleeding.

140
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:04,000
It's nothing.

141
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,120
Let's go to the hospital.

142
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:07,780
To the hospital? The same one from this morning?

143
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:10,860
The one from this morning.

144
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:14,760
Huo.

145
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:19,000
Huo, you're here.

146
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,900
Here for another inspection?

147
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:25,880
So you all know each other?

148
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:29,000
My brother used to come here once a week.

149
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,880
He's already a VIP customer here.

150
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:33,120
Haven't you heard the rumor?

151
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:36,000
Anyone my brother brings in for treating injuries

152
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,260
gets him a commission.

153
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,360
Take it easy, bro.

154
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:43,120
Huo.

155
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:45,240
Haven't seen you in ages.

156
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:47,520
Were you out of town or locked up?

157
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:50,200
Huo, I'd say we're destined to meet.

158
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:51,840
My first night shift after graduating

159
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:52,880
was operating on you.

160
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:54,280
Right here, remember?

161
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:56,400
You were quite a fighter.

162
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:57,720
Stop talking.

163
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:58,520
Please.

164
00:07:58,520 --> 00:07:59,650
Or I'll do it myself.

165
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:01,880
Now you want me to talk, but I'm done.

166
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:03,720
All finished.

167
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,400
Erpang,

168
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,720
call your uncle on the pager.

169
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:15,240
Don't call him.

170
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:16,920
I'm going home now.

171
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:19,440
I don't want to see him.

172
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:21,920
Seeing him will only make me upset.

173
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:24,040
Dad, don't be angry.

174
00:08:24,760 --> 00:08:26,640
It's my fault for not keeping him in line.

175
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:28,370
This has nothing to do with you.

176
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:30,680
I've been looking after him for over 30 years

177
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:32,320
and couldn't set him straight.

178
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:33,799
He's been like this since he was little.

179
00:08:33,799 --> 00:08:35,880
Always thinking the grass is greener elsewhere.

180
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:37,640
Never sticks with anything.

181
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:39,440
But he wasn't always

182
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:40,760
this desperate for money.

183
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:41,880
What's wrong with him?

184
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:43,039
Who knows.

185
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:44,920
Grandpa.

186
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:47,160
He saw that

187
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:49,760
Mengmeng's classmates all have Xiali cars.

188
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:51,040
He wants one too.

189
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:53,520
My uncle is so talented,

190
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:55,400
why doesn't he have money?

191
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:57,400
Your uncle's problem is

192
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:58,980
not that he lacks ability,

193
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:00,970
but that he has too many abilities.

194
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:04,240
A father knows his son best.

195
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:06,000
I can tell you

196
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,330
that in his entire life,

197
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:09,000
he'll never make much money.

198
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:11,440
Today,

199
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:14,280
my uncle and I made over 100 yuan

200
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:15,410
in just over an hour.

201
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:17,370
If someone hadn't interfered,

202
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:19,250
we could have made at least 800.

203
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:23,760
You're becoming more and more like your uncle.

204
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:26,880
That wasn't a compliment.

205
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:29,240
I meant you're becoming unreliable,

206
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:31,040
just like your uncle.

207
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:35,240
I think my uncle is great.

208
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:37,250
Whether he's good or not

209
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:38,820
remains to be seen.

210
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:43,640
My uncle just wants to help others.

211
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:47,120
He should help himself first. I'm leaving.

212
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:47,920
Dad.

213
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:50,000
Grandpa, let me walk you out.

214
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:50,800
No need.

215
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:54,640
If he continues to be this unreliable,

216
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:56,960
you should come back to my house.

217
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:59,380
I may not take perfect care of you,

218
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:01,400
but at least I won't lead you astray.

219
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:01,920
Right?

220
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:03,760
Better than following him

221
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:05,700
and picking up his bad habits.

222
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:07,160
Call him quickly.

223
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:08,920
Dad.

224
00:10:17,640 --> 00:10:19,040
Man,

225
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:20,440
what an amazing day.

226
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,800
Hang out with us,

227
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:26,240
and we guarantee every day will be amazing.

228
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:27,920
Right?

229
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:28,640
Yes,

230
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:30,240
my day has been amazing enough.

231
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:31,680
I'm going home to my wife.

232
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:33,320
Please take me home.

233
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:34,320
What home?

234
00:10:35,160 --> 00:10:35,920
We have to go sing karaoke

235
00:10:35,920 --> 00:10:36,920
and have some drinks.

236
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:37,680
What drinks?

237
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:39,640
You just got stitches and you want to go drinking?

238
00:10:39,640 --> 00:10:42,280
What does drinking have to do with getting stitches?

239
00:10:42,280 --> 00:10:43,760
We've all been busy all day.

240
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:44,640
Let's relax.

241
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:45,640
No, no.

242
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:46,520
You guys go relax.

243
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:47,380
I'm going home.

244
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:49,400
Cut the nonsense.

245
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:52,040
Don't you know we've spent the whole day for you?

246
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:54,680
Besides, we all know you sing well.

247
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:57,120
We're just waiting to hear you sing.

248
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:58,280
As the saying goes,

249
00:10:58,280 --> 00:10:59,680
there's no time like the present.

250
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:00,640
So it's settled.

251
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:01,920
Let's go.

252
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:03,160
Why don't you head back first?

253
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:04,120
What do you mean?

254
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:05,760
Aren't you just messing with me?

255
00:11:05,760 --> 00:11:06,560
I don't get it.

256
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,160
Drive faster.

257
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:20,840
Did you call your uncle earlier?

258
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:23,040
No.

259
00:11:24,280 --> 00:11:25,160
Call him

260
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:27,040
and tell him to come back.

261
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:28,640
Should I scare Uncle a bit?

262
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:31,200
Just leave him a message.

263
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:33,960
Say it's getting late

264
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,730
and he should come home.

265
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:37,720
Okay.

266
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:45,520
Brother,

267
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:46,920
do you really know

268
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:49,010
so many people at the hospital?

269
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:54,740
Well, they are important clients after all.

270
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:56,880
So if we go to the hospital in the future,

271
00:11:56,880 --> 00:11:58,680
will mentioning your name help?

272
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:01,970
It'll definitely work in surgery,

273
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:04,840
but not necessarily in other departments.

274
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:12,000
My wife wants me to go home.

275
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,800
Brother, I really have to leave.

276
00:12:14,560 --> 00:12:16,040
You shouldn't...

277
00:12:16,280 --> 00:12:17,280
You shouldn't...

278
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:25,000
It's okay to turn back even after falling into a trap.

279
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:27,480
Uncle,

280
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:32,360
Erpang's uncle, thank you

281
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:35,130
for taking care of Erpang all these years.

282
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,800
From now on, leave it to me.

283
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:41,160
You shouldn't...

284
00:12:41,160 --> 00:12:43,000
Eight things you shouldn't do...

285
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,320
You shouldn't...

286
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:47,960
surrender to fate.

287
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:52,120
I won't take back my tears,

288
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:56,600
